cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.Distributed, cs.SE, cs.PL

The paper discusses the challenges of confidentiality and performance in smart contracts on blockchains, which are topics typically covered in the computer security (cs.CR) and distributed computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. The use of Trusted Execution Environments (TEEs) also falls under these categories. The paper also discusses the architecture and implementation of the Ekiden system, which falls under the distributed systems (cs.Distributed) and software engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the pitfalls and attacks that can arise from hybridizing TEEs and blockchains, which falls under the programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category.
